Online Book Store System - Detailed Technical Documentation

---

1. Technical Architecture

Overview

The Online Book Store System is a MERN Stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js) based full-stack web application that enables users to browse, search, and purchase books online. It also provides an admin interface to manage books, users, and orders.

The application follows a layered and modular architecture, ensuring:

- Scalability (easy to expand features)
- Maintainability (clean code structure)
- Security (protected APIs and authentication)
- Performance (efficient data handling)

---

Architecture Layers

1. Client Layer (Frontend – React.js)

The client layer is responsible for user interaction and UI rendering. It communicates with the backend through REST APIs.

Functionalities

- User Registration and Login
- Book Browsing and Searching
- Viewing Book Details
- Add to Cart
- Checkout Process
- Order History Tracking
- Admin Dashboard

Responsibilities

- Sending API requests
- Handling responses
- Managing UI state
- Navigation using routing

---

2. API Layer (Backend – Express.js)

The API layer acts as a bridge between frontend and backend logic. It exposes RESTful APIs.

Responsibilities

- Handling HTTP Requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Authentication and Authorization (JWT)
- Routing Requests to Controllers
- Input Validation
- Error Handling

Example APIs

- POST /api/users/register
- POST /api/users/login
- GET /api/books
- POST /api/cart
- POST /api/orders

---

3. Service Layer (Business Logic)

This layer contains the core logic of the application and processes user actions.

Functions

- Cart Management
- Order Processing
- Inventory Checking
- User Authentication Logic
- Business Rules Implementation

---

4. Data Access Layer (Mongoose ODM)

This layer interacts with MongoDB using schemas and models.

Responsibilities

- Defining Schemas (User, Book, Order)
- Performing CRUD Operations
- Data Validation
- Query Execution

---

5. Database Layer (MongoDB)

MongoDB stores all persistent data in a structured format.

Stored Data

- User Credentials and Profiles
- Book Information (Title, Author, Price, Stock)
- Cart Items
- Orders and Transactions

